AB  - Environmental justice connects social injustices to environmental pollutants and anthropogenic climate change. One indicator of environmental injustice is access to green spaces, which provide urban heat island relief, mental health improvements, and noise and air pollution abatement. Larger green spaces are a unique type of green space because it’s size provides opportunities for outdoor recreation activities like camping, hiking, and backpacking, which are also important factors for mental and physical health. Considering the uneven access to green spaces, this research paper identified the barriers to access large green spaces in Oakland, California through survey and interview deployment. My findings indicated 1) access to large green spaces among demographic groups, 2) the importance of social organization and interaction when overcoming experiential and education barriers to large green spaces, and 3) desired amenities for large green spaces.
