AB  - Agriculture is the largest source of fresh water use in the world. In fact, many agricultural practice around the world uses water unsustainably, leading to surface and ground water depletion. International trade, one of the main drivers for agricultural production, also plays a role in causing water depletion. My study focuses on relationship between the international soy bean trade and water stress. I did that by calculating the unsustainably used water – defined as “water deficit (WD)”- embedded in the amount of soy beans exchanged between countries with available data from 2000 to 2016. By analyzing the spatial and temporal patterns of water deficit I found that countries that export greatest amounts of water deficit are United States, China, Spain, Argentina and Romania; countries that import the greatest amount of water deficits are Cyprus, Cuba, Azerbaijan, Costa Rica and Denmark. My results can serve as a reference for future researches on water deficit exchange among countries and for creating trade policies in response to water stress.
