AB  - Agricultural soil compaction has become more and more prevalent as mechanized agricultural using heavy equipment expands globally to feed a rapidly growing world population. However, there is limited knowledge and research being carried out on the biological and physical effects resulting from soil compaction. In our study, we found that in the compacted soil samples, there are increased soil fungi colony forming units and meso- and micro-fauna populations compared with un-compacted control soil. In addition, we found a significant decrease in aggregate stability in the compacted soil samples. Specifically, soil compaction destroys the physical environment including soil pore size and soil aggregates stability and these changes in turn it affect the soil organisms that inhabitat in these environments.
