AB  - Walnuts are an important California crop, and it is crucial for agricultural scientists to understand the biotic and abiotic interactions that affect the production of walnuts. Walnuts are highly susceptible to water stress, and drought conditions may have strong effects on walnut production. Walnuts are also affected by the walnut aphid (Chromaphis juglandicola), a prominent sap-sucking insect pest on walnut trees. Through an outdoor cage experiment, I researched the effect of soil water levels on walnut aphid (Chromaphis juglandicola) populations on walnut seedlings to determine effects of the California drought on this crop-pest system. The experiment found no significant difference between High, Medium, and Low drought treatments on aphid population composition. However, non-normal data indicates that a larger sample size was needed for conclusive results.
