AB  - Youth are particularly susceptible to obesity and other health conditions associated with unhealthy diet that are on the rise in the United States. In response, the San Francisco Bay Area has been the leader in youth healthy food programs. However, there is a lack of research on program assessment. To determine how programs were assessed, I conducted 19 surveys and 13 interviews with program leaders from around the Bay Area. I found that some program leaders were uncomfortable with assessment, as they associated formal evaluations with government bureaucracy. Others desired the ability to assess programs, but lacked the funding to do so. Because of this, leaders of newer programs expressed concerns about a lack of information on successful programs in the area. My findings suggest that resources on how to conduct formal assessment should be provided to program leaders.
