AU  - Chris Cottrell
TI  - Landowner Mapping in the Yountville Gap
PY  - 1999
PB  - University of California, Berkeley
UR  - https://www.ocf.berkeley.edu/~pkmendez/envsci/projects/1999final/CornishP_1999.pdf
U1  - CornishP_1999-page1.pdf
AB  - Outdoor enthusiasts, conservationists and land use planners have been working in collaboration with the Bay Area Ridge Trail Council to establish a multi-use, ridgeline trail that would circumnavigate the entire San Francisco Bay. To date 210 miles of the over 400 mile, nine-county trail have been established using existing municipal, regional and state park trails, and through acquisition of lands or use of easements on private lands. There are numerous gaps of unconnected trail remaining; this project focuses on the landowners of Napa County's "Yountville Gap". The ultimate goal of the study was to create a landowner map for the use of the Napa County Committee of the Bay Area Ridge Trail Council. Landowner data was collected from the Napa County Assesor's Office. Three hundred and seventy-three properities were studied, covering a total of 15, 073 acres. Private property dominated the ownership types; 309 of the properties were privately owned; the land area of these parcels was 10,066 acres. Twenty four properties were coded for business use, covering 1,637 acres. Public lands made up over 16% of the Yountville Gap with 24 properties covering 2,452 acres. Thirteen properties were coded as Open Space, for a total of 713 acres. The study also examines other trails and recommended hiking areas in the valley; using local guidebooks, it was determined that the majority (87%) of publicly accesible hiking trails in the valley are situated on public lands.
