UR  - https://www.ocf.berkeley.edu/~pkmendez/envsci/projects/1999final/JungJ_1999.pdf
U1  - JungJ_1999-page1.pdf
AB  - This thesis project is to look for possible nitrogen pollution in Wildcat Creek. I proposed that the agricultural practices performed on the course were polluting the creek and the downstream ecosystems. I tested the water and aquatic ecosystems by measuring nitrates, pH, electrical conductivity, and plant and algae densities. The results show a high amount of nitrates coinciding with high plant and algae densities at two specific points along Wildcat Creek. The remaining sites do not exhibit characteristics of nitrogen pollution, though. I concluded that there was a nitrogen input from the golf course, but it did not greatly effect downstream ecosystems.
