AU  - Danny Kwak
TI  - Oxidation Kinetics of Ferrous Chelates of Dimercaptosuccinate in Aqueous Solution
PY  - 1999
PB  - University of California, Berkeley
UR  - https://www.ocf.berkeley.edu/~pkmendez/envsci/projects/1999final/KlirisJ_1999.pdf
U1  - KlirisJ_1999-page1.pdf
AB  - The kinetics of Fe"(DMSA) oxidation with oxygen were studied for the
control of NO in wet scrubber systems. The order of reaction with respect to 02 was found
to be one by varying the [02] from 3 mg/L (93.8 u,M) to 20 mg/L (625 pJvl) and keeping
[Fel!] in excess. The order ofreaction with respect to Fe" was found to be one by varying
[Fe11] from 2.5 mM to 5 mM. The rate constant, k, was 0.03 M"'s"' at 5°C. The temperature
of the reaction was varied from 5-20°C to determine the apparent activation energy. All
experiments were carried out at pH = 5. The results show that the oxidation of Fe (DMSA)
has an apparent activation energy = 52 kJ/mol. The implications for the design of wet
scrubber systems are discussed.
