TI  - Looking at Agroecology as a Means to Revive Haiti’s Agricultural Condition
PY  - 1999
PB  - University of California, Berkeley
UR  - https://www.ocf.berkeley.edu/~pkmendez/envsci/projects/1999final/LouisWG_1999.pdf
U1  - LouisWG_1999-page1.pdf
AB  - Haiti, like many of the Caribbean islands, suffers greatly from famine and environmental degradation. The existing agricultural system has failed to provide enough food for its population. The present condition demands immediate attention. This paper analyzes the potential of Agroecology to remedy some of the country’s agricultural and ecological conditions by studying the application of its techniques in other countries. This study and drawing on interviews with persons who are familiar with the country’s situation suggests that agroecology, when used properly, can indeed relieve Haiti’s environmental problems. With its implementation the people may for once, with an increase in agricultural production and reduction of land degradation, enjoy the benefits of a thriving economy and environment.
