TI  - Public Transportation Services Between Marin County and
San Francisco
PY  - 1999
PB  - University of California, Berkeley
UR  - https://www.ocf.berkeley.edu/~pkmendez/envsci/projects/1999final/WangHS_1999.pdf
U1  - WangHS_1999-page1.pdf
AB  - The Golden Gate Bridge and the Highway 101 corridor in the North Bay are
two of the most highly congested spots in the San Francisco Bay Area. During commute
hours, the number of vehicles on Highway 101 is well above the maximum capacity of the
roadway. Based on commuter surveys and transit plan reviews, this study concludes that in
order to solve the congestion problem on the Golden Gate Bridge and Highway 101, there
should be a high level of cooperation between transit agencies and city planners. Also, each
transit alternatives should be studied extensively until a long-term, cost-effective alternative is
found.
