AB  - Two factors which affect erosion, slope and ground cover, were measured in Strawberry Canyon, a riparian area which is located less than one mile east of the UC Berkeley main campus. The ground cover types estimated were moss, litter, rocks, large branches, and vegetation. Also estimated were cover at a 30 cm height and canopy cover. There was little noticeable relationship between slope or cover with respect to erosion in this study. It appears that there may more factors affecting erosion than slope and vegetation at the study sites.
