AB  - Eight grassland species were grown under 360 and 720 ppm carbon dioxide concentrations in controlled chambers to compare final dry mass. Annual grassland species were collected from the experimental site which are: Bromus hordeacus, Avena barbata, Plantago lanceolata, Anagallis arvensis, Geranium dissectum, Lotus wrangelianus, Trifolium hirtum and Vicia sativa. The plants were grown in sandstone soil in controlled chambers with ambient levels of atmospheric CO₂ and experimental chambers with double ambient values of CO₂. Water and fertilizer were not applied, they were watered only by natural conditions. Biomass data is unavailable for Lotus. The other plants’ biomass data reveal that they had similar mass despite the type of treatment. A reconsideration of the hypothesis is essential.
