AB  - To investigate the relationship between toxin concentrations from the Elkhorn Slough and Moss Landing State Beach, mussels were collected from a site within the Slough and a site at Moss Landing in order to be tested for DDE, DDD, and DDT. The mussels were put through the California Department of Food and Agriculture Organochlorine Pesticide Screen (AOAC 1995) and DDE, DDD, and DDT concentrations were determined. Through a two sided Z-test at the 1% significance level, I found a significant difference in DDE concentrations between the Elkhorn Slough and Moss Landing. There was a trend of decreasing concentration of DDE from the Slough to Moss Landing, which is to be expected because of Moss Landing's direct exposure to the ocean. Although the DDE concentrations at Moss Landing are more diluted than the Elkhorn Slough's, Moss Landing still receives DDE from the Slough.
