AU  - Timur Nusratty
TI  - Assessment of Possible Substance Loading in Strawberry Creek due to Runoff from the Owners' Leasing System Cogeneration Plant on the University of California at Berkeley Campus
PY  - 1997
PB  - University of California, Berkeley
UR  - https://www.ocf.berkeley.edu/~pkmendez/envsci/projects/1997final/NusrattyT_1997.pdf
U1  - NusrattyT_1997-page1.pdf
AB  - My thesis project involved the assumption that the OLS Cogeneration Plant on the University of California at Berkeley Campus was polluting nearby Strawberry Creek (the natural ornament of the campus). I hypothesized that the waste water derived from condensate cleansing activities of the cogeneration plant did not contain substances at EPA determined toxic levels, and that the waste water did not leak into Strawberry Creek and alter its chemistry. To prove my hypotheses, I tested nine water quality parameters at five sites, three times a day for four days, and once I had determined mean concentrations and measurements, I compared the test results to EPA surface water quality standards. All of the test results fell well below the EPA standards, and because of this, I upheld my alternate hypotheses. In conclusion, I claim that the activities of the waste water derived from the OLS plant condensate polishing activities does not contain substances at toxic levels, and the waste water does not alter the chemistry of Strawberry Creek.
